6 "Section 1. R.S. 17:3384 is hereby enacted to read as follows:
7 §3384. Public postsecondary education institutions; tuition and fee authority
8 and autonomy
9 A. Notwithstanding any other provision of law to the contrary, each
10 public postsecondary education institution may to establish and adjust tuition
11 and fee amounts for all programs offered by the institution, including
12 granting certificates, degrees, diplomas, or other credentials of value. This
13 authority includes establishing tuition and fee amounts for part-time students,
14 dual enrollment students, and students enrolled in summer and intersession
15 terms.
16 B. When establishing tuition and fee amounts, each public
17 postsecondary education institution shall, at a minimum, consider the
18 following:
19 (1) Tuition and fee amounts of peer institutions.
20 (2) Median household income in Louisiana and in states where peer
21 institutions are located.
22 (3) Affordability.
23 (4) Total cost of attendance.
24 C. Each public postsecondary education institution shall establish a
25 process for providing adequate notice to students of tuition and fee amounts.
26 Prior to imposing any increase in tuition and fee amounts pursuant to this
27 Section, each institution shall establish criteria for waivers in cases of
28 financial hardship. Such information shall be made available to all current
29 and prospective students affected by the increase in a timely manner.
30 D. Each public postsecondary education institution shall submit a
31 written report to its management board, the Board of Regents, the House
32 Committee on Education, the Senate Committee on Education, the House
33 Committee on Appropriations, and the Senate Committee on Finance not
34 later than February fifteenth annually regarding how the tuition and
35 mandatory fees authorized by this Section are being implemented."
